# 1. Executive Overview

AFAT-X10 (Advanced Funnel Acceleration Thrust) is a conceptual aerodynamic propulsion augmentation architecture designed to improve aircraft efficiency by capturing, compressing, redirecting, and accelerating airflow through specially engineered fuselage channels.

Unlike conventional aircraft that primarily use engines to generate thrust, AFAT-X10 seeks to use portions of the aircraft structure itself as an active aerodynamic energy management system.

The architecture focuses on:

* Airflow capture
* Pressure amplification
* Controlled acceleration
* Drag reduction
* Structural stabilization
* Propulsion efficiency enhancement

---

# 2. Core Design Objective

Traditional aircraft:

```text
Engine
   ↓
Thrust
   ↓
Aircraft Motion
```

AFAT-X10 introduces:

```text
Atmospheric Flow
        ↓
Capture
        ↓
Compression
        ↓
Acceleration
        ↓
Redistribution
        ↓
Supplemental Thrust
```

The intention is to recover useful aerodynamic energy from airflow already interacting with the aircraft.

